deck: Paalko is one of the six new guardians of the Green Lantern universe.
description:
Paalko is one of the six new guardians that have taken the mantle of Guardians of the Universe, after Sinestro and Atrocitus killed the previous guardians.

Rise of the Third Army

For eons, Paalko and the other guardians were hidden and sealed as wardens in the Chamber of Shadows, along with Volthoom, the First Lantern, who they were assigned to oversee. When Paalko and the other guardians finally come face-to-face with their estranged siblings, they are shocked to see how emotionless the latter have become and briefly provide resistance, which results in one of Paalko's brothers being killed. They are again locked into the Chamber of Shadows until finally Simon Baz releases them.

Later, after Volthoom and the Guardians (save for Ganthet and Sayd) are killed, Paalko and the other guardians step into the role of Guardians of the Universe, though they relinquish their responsibility to Hal Jordan in order to experience the universe they had been earlier denied.

Light's Out

Paalko and the others begin playing a larger role at the end of Light's Out. After their voyage across the universe, they seem to have been caught up to speed on the comings-and-goings and are able to aid Kyle Rayner as both a white lantern and the host of the emotional spectrum's entities. With the end of Light's Out, they are seen surveying the wall that protects whatever is beyond the edge of the universe and become the only beings that know of Kyle Rayner's survival.

Paalko seems to have a romantic relationship with his 'sister' Zalla. Zalla and Paalko, out of the other Templar Guardians, also appear to be the closest allies of Kyle Rayner.

Origin

When Maria starts hearing stories of dinosaurs in jungle of Columbia, South America she seeks them out only to find Turok the Dinosaur Hunter is killing them. She requests his help to capture them for the purpose of breeding them, unaware that these dinosaurs are bio-genetically intelligent creatures and not the animals she thinks they are. Turok refuses to help but Maria gets her way when she discovers that they are reproducing without Turkos help.

deck: Dinah Drake was the original Black Canary of the Golden Age, and mother of Dinah Laurel Lance, the modern Black Canary.
description:
This page is for the original Black Canary, Dinah Drake Lance. Her daughter, Dinah Laurel Lance, is the second Black Canary.

Character History

Pre-Crisis

Dinah Drake was a child in a long line of police officers, and she honored that legacy by taking to the streets as a costumed crime fighter. Dinah was a member of the Justice Society of America, having taken Johnny Thunder's place on the team.

Dinah Drake married police detective Larry Lance, and had a daughter Dinah Lance. However, her daughter was cursed by Wizard to have a lethal sonic scream. So, Dinah called on an old friend to put her in help her daughter, Johnny Thunder. The only way he could save her was to put her in suspended animation, and, as he felt it was better for everyone, he made Dinah and Larry believe their daughter had died as a baby.

Later, Larry sacrifices his life to save Dinah from Aquarius. In her grief Dinah travels to Earth-1 from Earth-2, where she joins the Justice League and finds that she has gained the superpower of a sonic scream, her "canary cry".

However, she later discovers that she was poisoned by radiation from the battle with Aquarius, and was dying. So, she had her memories transferred to her now adult daughter's body, and so the Black Canary of Earth-1 was really Dinah Lance's body with her mother's memory.

Post Crisis

After Crisis on Infinite Earths, Black Canary's origins are altered. Dinah Drake was the original Black Canary, who was a part of the Justice Society of America. She married Larry Lance and had her daughter, Dinah Laurel Lance.

After Larry's death, Dinah raised their daughter on her own. Dinah Lance grew up around her mother's friends of the Justice Society, and aspired to be a superhero, like her mother. However, Dinah Drake did not approve.
